    },
    {
        "text": "For the few weeks cherries are at their best I eat them all day long.  Straight from the paper bag on the way home from the shops, baked into cakes and brownies (see page 293), to top pancakes (see page SERVES 2 290) or laid over a bowl of ice for a quick dessert on a hot day. This is how I get cherries into my mornings and their cheering colour never fails to lift my spirits. Almond butter works here to give this smoothie an almost marzipan note; it works with frozen cherries, too once summer is gone.",
        "topic": {
            "blurb": 1.0,
            "ingredient": 0.0,
            "method": 0.0,
            "other": 0.0,
            "title": 0.0
        }
    },
