            "other": 0.0,
            "title": 0.0
        }
    },
    {
        "text": "300g brown rice syrup",
        "topic": {
            "blurb": 0.0,
            "ingredient": 1.0,
            "method": 0.0,
            "other": 0.0,
            "title": 0.0
        }
    },
    {
        "text": "100g coconut oil, plus extra for greasing",
        "topic": {
            "blurb": 0.0,
            "ingredient": 1.0,
            "method": 0.0,
            "other": 0.0,
            "title": 0.0
        }
    },
    {
        "text": "My new addiction. I was sceptical about a savoury snack bar, but these are as moreish as they are balanced: salty olives and nori (sheets of dried seaweed used to wrap sushi), buttery sesame seeds, toasted oats, crunchy puffed rice and a hint of sweetness.  If you are struggling to find brown rice syrup, you could use runny honey, but they won't set quite as firm, so be sure to store the bars in the fridge. This is a recipe from my column in the Guardian; | have made them so many times since it was printed | felt | had to include it here.",
        "topic": {
            "blurb": 1.0,
            "ingredient": 0.0,
            "method": 0.0,
            "other": 0.0,
            "title": 0.0
        }
    },
    {
        "text": "Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/180\u00b0C fan/gas 6. Put the nori sheets on one baking tray and the oats on another. Bake for 3-5 minutes, or until the nori has darkened a little and crumbles easily in your hand and the oats smell toasty.",
        "topic": {
            "blurb": 0.0,
            "ingredient": 0.0,
            "method": 1.0,
            "other": 0.0,
            "title": 0.0
        }
    },
    {
        "text": "Grease a 20 x 30cm baking tray with coconut oif. Mix all the dry ingredients, including the olives, together ina large bowl and set aside,",
        "topic": {
            "blurb": 0.0,
            "ingredient": 0.0,
            "method": 1.0,
            "other": 0.0,
            "title": 0.0
        }
    },
    {
        "text": "Combine the rice syrup and coconut oil in a small Saucepan over a medium heat. Stir for a minute or two until it melts and thickens little ~ this will take about 4 minutes. Pour the coconut oil mixture over the oat mixture and stir until everything is well mixed.",
        "topic": {
            "blurb": 0.0,
            "ingredient": 0.0,
            "method": 1.0,
            "other": 0.0,
            "title": 0.0
        }
    },
    {
        "text": "Spread the mixture out in the tin and press down firmly; this will help your bars stick together. Chill for a few hours before cutting into bars \u2014 1 go for about 16, but you could make them bigger or Smaller as you wish. They will keep in the fridge for up to a week.",
        "topic": {
            "blurb": 0.0,
            "ingredient": 0.0,
            "method": 1.0,
            "other": 0.0,
            "title": 0.0
        }
    },
    {
